Documentation review — current state
=====================================


DONE
────

✅ Getting Started turbulence section
   Replaced "If something does not converge" (too polite, too structured) with
   "What usually breaks first" — a story-driven breakdown of what actually goes wrong
   at Day-0, in the order it happens. Controller doesn't seed, FETCH stalls at MinIO,
   health says green but doctor disagrees, auth wrong command name, Envoy restart order.
   Also fixed the "healthy" checklist to be more explicit about what the health command
   misses.

✅ Known Issues restructured into 4 buckets
   - Product limitations (split-horizon, single-node data loss, no release tarball, etc.)
   - Infrastructure bugs (DNS persistence, Envoy/xDS order, ScyllaDB migration split-brain)
   - CLI gaps (missing commands + wrong names, with MCP/gRPC workarounds)
   - Documentation mismatches (wrong port, wrong path, removed commands still referenced)
   Each entry is self-contained: symptom, cause, workaround, status.

✅ Platform Status page (operators/platform-status.md)
   Full Implemented / Partial / Planned / Not Supported inventory per feature area.

✅ Versioning expanded (developers/versioning.md)
   version vs build_id model, 4-layer flow diagram, downgrade guard, exact-replay
   connection, v1.0.0 criteria with honest current status.

✅ Developer value proposition (writing-a-microservice.md)
   "Why build on Globular instead of plain systemd + gRPC?" table added.

✅ node.recover.full_reseed documentation (operators/node-recovery.md)
   601 lines. Safety invariants, all phases, CLI reference, 10-step procedure,
   failure handling, FAQ. Full cross-linking from failure-scenarios, tasks/recover-node,
   index.

✅ Known issues fixed in code
   - Bootstrap flag file: os.Remove() after expiry detection in security/bootstrap.go
   - ACME cert path mismatch: ensureXDSSymlink() in domain/reconciler.go creates
     /var/lib/globular/config/tls/acme/{fqdn} → /var/lib/globular/domains/{fqdn}
     automatically on every reconcile pass. No more manual symlink required.
   - Wrong command names fixed across 17 doc files (auth set-password, services repair,
     backup run → root-passwd, get-drift-report / node repair, backup create)

✅ Developer narrative docs (local-first.md, service-packaging.md, workflow-integration.md)
   Added design-reasoning layer to all three:
   - local-first.md: why Globular inverted infrastructure-first, config fallback chain
     as intentional design, not convenience; "Designing for Local-First" framing
   - service-packaging.md: why tgz not Docker/deb/rpm, why spec is separate from binary,
     why build numbers exist separately from versions, why priority exists beyond deps
   - workflow-integration.md: why workflow integration inverts operational control,
     why VERIFY is separate from START, why services declare their own backup datasets,
     data class trade-offs (backup cost vs recovery cost), why graceful shutdown
     matters specifically for convergence upgrades


